Create a shared helper component that resolves `iconId` to the correct logo component from `ADAPTER_LOGO_MAP`, with a fallback to the Lucide `Bot` icon.

## Implementation

Create `apps/client/src/layers/features/relay/ui/AdapterIcon.tsx`:

```typescript
import { ADAPTER_LOGO_MAP, type AdapterLogoProps } from '@dorkos/icons/adapter-logos';
import { Bot } from 'lucide-react';

interface AdapterIconProps extends AdapterLogoProps {
  /** Adapter icon identifier from the manifest. */
  iconId?: string;
  /** Adapter type -- used as fallback lookup key when iconId is absent. */
  adapterType?: string;
}

/** Resolves an adapter's iconId to the corresponding brand logo component. */
export function AdapterIcon({ iconId, adapterType, size = 16, className }: AdapterIconProps) {
  const Logo = ADAPTER_LOGO_MAP[iconId ?? ''] ?? ADAPTER_LOGO_MAP[adapterType ?? ''];
  if (Logo) return <Logo size={size} className={className} />;
  return <Bot className={className} style={{ width: size, height: size }} />;
}
```

This component:
1. First tries to look up `iconId` in the `ADAPTER_LOGO_MAP`
2. Falls back to looking up `adapterType` (since built-in adapter iconIds match their type)
3. Falls back to the Lucide `Bot` icon for unknown adapter types

The component lives in the `features/relay/ui/` directory following FSD conventions. It imports from `@dorkos/icons/adapter-logos` (cross-package, not a layer violation) and `lucide-react` (external dependency).

Also export `AdapterIcon` from the relay feature barrel if one exists, or ensure it's importable from its direct path within the features layer.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Component renders the correct logo for known iconIds (`telegram`, `slack`, `claude-code`, `webhook`, `telegram-chatsdk`)
- Component falls back to `adapterType` lookup when `iconId` is undefined
- Component renders Lucide `Bot` icon when neither `iconId` nor `adapterType` match
- `size` prop controls the icon dimensions
- `className` prop is passed through for styling
- No FSD layer violations

Replace the local `PLATFORM_ICONS` map and `PlatformIcon` component in `AdapterNode.tsx` with the shared `AdapterIcon` component.

## Implementation

Edit `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/ui/AdapterNode.tsx`.

1. Remove these imports (line 4):
```typescript
// REMOVE: MessageSquare, Webhook, Bot from lucide-react
import { MessageSquare, Webhook, Bot, Plus } from 'lucide-react';
// REPLACE with:
import { Plus } from 'lucide-react';
```

2. Add import:
```typescript
import { AdapterIcon } from '@/layers/features/relay/ui/AdapterIcon';
```
Note: This is a features-layer cross-module UI import, which is allowed by FSD rules (UI composition across features is permitted).

3. Remove the `PLATFORM_ICONS` map (lines ~49-52):
```typescript
// REMOVE entirely:
const PLATFORM_ICONS: Record<string, React.ElementType> = {
  telegram: MessageSquare,
  webhook: Webhook,
};
```

4. Replace the `PlatformIcon` component (lines ~55-58):
```typescript
// REMOVE:
function PlatformIcon({ adapterType }: { adapterType: string }) {
  const Icon = PLATFORM_ICONS[adapterType] ?? Bot;
  return <Icon className="text-muted-foreground size-4 shrink-0" />;
}

// REPLACE with:
/** Renders the platform icon for an adapter type. Extracted as a component to satisfy React Compiler. */
function PlatformIcon({ adapterType }: { adapterType: string }) {
  return <AdapterIcon adapterType={adapterType} size={16} className="text-muted-foreground shrink-0" />;
}
```

The `PlatformIcon` wrapper is kept as a thin adapter to preserve the existing call sites in `AdapterCompactPill` and `AdapterDefaultCard` without changing their props.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `PLATFORM_ICONS` map is removed
- `MessageSquare`, `Webhook`, `Bot` imports from lucide-react are removed (only `Plus` remains)
- `PlatformIcon` delegates to `AdapterIcon` with `size={16}`
- All adapter types render their correct brand logo in the topology graph
- Unknown types fall back to Lucide `Bot` via `AdapterIcon`
- No FSD layer violations (features/mesh importing features/relay UI is allowed)

Update `AdapterCardHeader.test.tsx` to reflect the schema change from `iconEmoji` to `iconId` and the rendering change from emoji spans to SVG components.

## Implementation

Edit `apps/client/src/layers/features/relay/ui/__tests__/AdapterCardHeader.test.tsx`.

### 1. Update fixture (line ~19)
```typescript
// BEFORE:
iconEmoji: '\uD83D\uDCE8',

// AFTER:
iconId: 'telegram',
```

### 2. Update the emoji rendering test (lines ~110-113)
```typescript
// BEFORE:
it('renders the icon emoji', () => {
  render(<AdapterCardHeader {...defaultProps()} />);
  expect(screen.getByText('\uD83D\uDCE8')).toBeInTheDocument();
});

// AFTER:
it('renders the adapter icon', () => {
  const { container } = render(<AdapterCardHeader {...defaultProps()} />);
  // AdapterIcon renders an SVG for known iconIds
  const svg = container.querySelector('svg');
  expect(svg).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

The test now checks for the presence of an SVG element instead of emoji text, since `AdapterIcon` renders inline SVGs for known adapter types.

### 3. Verify all other tests still pass
The remaining tests (primary name, category badge, switch toggle, kebab menu) should pass without changes since they don't depend on the icon rendering.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `baseManifest` fixture uses `iconId: 'telegram'` instead of `iconEmoji`
- Emoji text assertion is replaced with SVG element assertion
- All existing tests pass
- No `role="img"` assertions remain (SVGs use `aria-hidden` instead)
- Test runs successfully: `pnpm vitest run apps/client/src/layers/features/relay/ui/__tests__/AdapterCardHeader.test.tsx`

Update `CatalogCard.test.tsx` to reflect the schema change from `iconEmoji` to `iconId` and the rendering change from emoji spans to SVG components.

## Implementation

Edit `apps/client/src/layers/features/relay/ui/__tests__/CatalogCard.test.tsx`.

### 1. Update the icon rendering test (lines ~42-48)
```typescript
// BEFORE:
it('renders icon emoji when provided', () => {
  const manifest: AdapterManifest = { ...baseManifest, iconEmoji: '\uD83D\uDCAC' };
  render(<CatalogCard manifest={manifest} onAdd={vi.fn()} />);

  expect(screen.getByRole('img', { hidden: true })).toBeInTheDocument();
  expect(screen.getByText('\uD83D\uDCAC')).toBeInTheDocument();
});

// AFTER:
it('renders adapter icon when iconId provided', () => {
  const manifest: AdapterManifest = { ...baseManifest, iconId: 'slack' };
  const { container } = render(<CatalogCard manifest={manifest} onAdd={vi.fn()} />);

  // AdapterIcon renders an SVG for known iconIds
  const svg = container.querySelector('svg');
  expect(svg).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

### 2. Update the missing icon test (lines ~50-54)
```typescript
// BEFORE:
it('does not render icon emoji when not provided', () => {
  render(<CatalogCard manifest={baseManifest} onAdd={vi.fn()} />);

  expect(screen.queryByRole('img', { hidden: true })).not.toBeInTheDocument();
});

// AFTER:
it('renders fallback icon when iconId not provided', () => {
  const { container } = render(<CatalogCard manifest={baseManifest} onAdd={vi.fn()} />);

  // AdapterIcon always renders -- falls back to Bot icon (also an SVG)
  const svg = container.querySelector('svg');
  expect(svg).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

Note: The `baseManifest` fixture at the top of the file does NOT have `iconEmoji` set (it's optional), so it already tests the fallback case. Since `AdapterIcon` always renders (either a brand logo or Bot fallback), the test now asserts that an SVG is present rather than absent.

### 3. Verify remaining tests pass
The other tests (display name, description, category badge, onAdd callback, category colors) should pass without changes.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `iconEmoji` references removed from all test cases
- Icon present test uses `iconId: 'slack'` and asserts SVG renders
- Icon absent test renamed to "fallback" test and asserts Bot SVG renders
- `role="img"` assertions removed (SVGs use `aria-hidden`)
- All tests pass: `pnpm vitest run apps/client/src/layers/features/relay/ui/__tests__/CatalogCard.test.tsx`
